title: Dani Profita leads Warren Hills field hockey team to Hunterdon/Warren/Sussex title
text:
Junior forward Dani Profita scored twice on Saturday as Warren Hills Regional High School rallied for a 2-1 victory over Hunterdon Central in the Hunterdon/Warren/Sussex title game at Hackettstown High School. 
It was the Blue Streaks' third straight H/W/S title. 
Hunterdon Central struck first when Jill Murray scored off a corner with 3:20 elapsed in the second half. 
Profita scored the equalizer less than three minutes later on an assist from Mikayla Dugan . Profita then tallied the deciding goal on a feed from Rachel Phillips with 12:37 remaining. It was Profita's team-leading 30th goal of the season. 
Blue Streaks goalie Jackie de Raismes stopped six shots to preserve the win.
